verblex: 1. To move through the water by making movements with your arms and legs. English = swim.
2. To swim breast stroke. English = breast-stroke.
nomlex: 1. The sport or recreation in which people move through the water by making movements with your arms and legs. English = swimming.
2. A short period of activity during which people move through the water by making movements with your arms and legs. English = swim.
3. A style of swimming. English = breast stroke.
